AIM: 
To write a C program to calculate the area of a triangle using the formula: - √S(S-A)(S-B)(S-C) 
where S =(A+B+C)/2;

ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare variables a, b, c for the sides of the triangle, s for semi-perimeter, and area for 
storing the result. 
3. Read the three sides of the triangle from the user. 
4. Compute semi-perimeter: 
5. Use the formula: 
6. using sqrt() from <math.h>. 
7. Display the area. 
8. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM: 
#include <stdio.h> 
#include <math.h> 
int main() { 
float a, b, c, s, area; 
printf("Enter side a: "); 
scanf("%f", &a); 
printf("Enter side b: "); 
scanf("%f", &b); 
printf("Enter side c: "); 
scanf("%f", &c); 
s = (a + b + c) / 2; 
area = sqrt(s * (s - a) * (s - b) * (s - c));  
printf("Area of the triangle = %.2f\n", area); 
return 0; 
} 

